title: Live Aid campaigner Bob Geldof was ‘scathing about African leaders’, files reveal
description: Singer urged Tony Blair not to appoint African co-chair to commission on aid, UK government papers showThe Live Aid campaigner Bob Geldof urged Tony Blair not to appoint an African co-chair to the UK-led organisation working to overhaul international aid to the continent because he thought African leadership was “very weak” on the issue, newly released government documents suggest.The singer was “scathing about the ability and worthiness of virtually all African leaders” before the establishment in 2004 of Blair’s Commission for Africa, which would produce a report, Our Common Interest, and prompt a landmark pledge by rich nations to boost aid and write off debt. Continue reading...
author: Caroline Davies

title: Jimmy Carter's heartwarming airline tradition: 'He shook hands with each person on plane'
description: Jimmy Carter, the 39th President of the United States, passed away at age 100. He was remembered for his integrity, humanitarian efforts, and personal kindness, such as greeting every passenger on his Delta flights. Carter was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize in 2002 and was deeply involved with Habitat for Humanity. His legacy endures through The Carter Center.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Georgia judge found dead in courtroom on final day of term
description: Effingham County state court Judge Stephen Yekel was found dead from a self-inflicted gunshot wound on his last day in office. Authorities believe the incident occurred the night before. Yekel had served the legal profession for over 45 years and had attempted to resign after losing his re-election bid.
author: TOI World Desk
